<h2>Itinerary for self guided multicentre holiday</h2>
<p><strong>Day 1 </strong></p>
<p>Arrive at Zurich airport and transfer to the lakeside resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef}" title="Lucerne">Lucerne</a> (approx. 1 hour). Check into your hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 </strong></p>
<p>Walk through Lucerne’s quaint Old Town with its traffic-free streets and frescoed buildings and historic monuments including the must-see ‘Chapel Bridge’. In the afternoon, is time to discover the region, perhaps take a boat ride on the stunning lake with the option to visit Mount Pilatus and Mount Rigi for walking terrain and superb views.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 (Monday)</strong></p>
<p>A day of leisure or activity as there are excellent hiking opportunities here, with easy access from the city via boat and mountain transport to the vast Lake Lucerne region. Perhaps visit the neighbouring resorts of <a data-udi="umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6}" title="Weggis">Weggis</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/3d1595c705ff4dd7b811ee9f3e9ece6c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3d1595c705ff4dd7b811ee9f3e9ece6c}" title="Vitznau">Vitznau</a> whilst <a data-udi="umb://document/7456bae57241449a84a68959b62b2aba" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7456bae57241449a84a68959b62b2aba}" title="Interlaken">Interlaken</a> with its lakes <a data-udi="umb://document/7d838fa65a44467f9a85c30c8d2de877" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d838fa65a44467f9a85c30c8d2de877}" title="Lake Thun">Thun</a> and Brienz, is also within easy reach.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 </strong></p>
<p>Leave Lucerne for the stylish resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/cc17fe79ccd1491a92608658d3af9d55" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc17fe79ccd1491a92608658d3af9d55}" title="St. Moritz">St. Moritz</a> (approx. 4 hours). Relax this afternoon with a gentle stroll down the main promenade, browse the shops and enjoy an optional delicious hot chocolate in one of the many cafés.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 </strong></p>
<p>This is a day trip from St Moritz to Tirano. The Journey down to Tirano will be in 2nd class and the return journey will be in 1st class. </p>
<p><strong>Day 6 </strong></p>
<p>A day to explore St. Moritz’s splendid Engadine countryside and cool off in one of the region’s lakes. Perhaps take a day hike to Corvatsch or Corviglia for inspiring 360° views along a panoramic trail – guests have unlimited use of resort’s mountain transport included.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 </strong></p>
<p>The journey from St Moritz to Chur will be on a standard train where you will change to the Glacier Express. Trains depart at 2 minutes past the hour from St Moritz and the journey time is 2 hours to Chur. At Chur, you will take the Glacier Express, number 907, which departs Chur at 14.16 and arrives into Zermatt at 20.10 ( these are approximate times). Lunch will be available to you from Chur to Zermatt and you will arrive into Zermatt in time for dinner at your hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 </strong></p>
<p>A day to explore Zermatt and really soak up the traditional Swiss ambience. Take a stroll through the enchanting traffic-free streets, discovering the many shops and cafés and discover the Old Village known as ‘Hinterdorf’ home to more than 30 buildings over 500 years old constructed in the traditional style of barns and stores of Upper Valais.</p>
<p><strong>Day 9 </strong></p>
<p>Another day with the choice to explore independently the 21 mountain cable cars, cog railways and gondolas which open up the vast hiking network or book an optional excursion during your time in Zermatt. Enjoy a journey on the iconic Gornergrat railway and marvel at the backdrop of the Matterhorn.</p>
<p><strong>Day 10 </strong></p>
<p>Transfer to Zurich airport for your return journey home (approx. 3 hours) or extend your stay and transfer to the Alpine ‘Eiger village’ of <a data-udi="umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da}" title="Grindelwald">Grindelwald</a> in the Bernese Oberland.</p>
<p><strong>Day 11 onwards - Optional stay in Switzerland</strong></p>
<p>The option to stay extra nights in Zermatt or add on additional nights in Grindelwald or Interlaken.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>What’s included</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Discount travel card included, worth over £100</li>
<li>Scheduled return flights from the UK to Switzerland</li>
<li>9 nights half board throughout in 4-star hotels. All rooms with private facilities</li>
<li>Full day excursion on the spectacular Bernina Express train from St. Moritz to Tirano</li>
<li>Full day excursion on the famous Glacier Express train from St. Moritz to Zermatt with 3 courses lunch included</li>
<li>1st class rail transfers throughout (some change of trains required)</li>
<li>Services of Inghams representative in some resorts or by telephone</li>
<li>Time to relax and enjoy Zermatt with optional Gornergrat and Matterhorn excursions</li>
<li>Walking opportunities in St. Moritz with free unlimited use of lifts</li>
</ul>
<p>You'll enjoy half board meals on this tour with continental hot &amp; cold buffet breakfast and 4 courses evening meal for dinner (drinks are excluded). In the Parkhotel Beaus Site in Zermatt, the evening meal is a set course.</p>
<p><strong>Extras:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All excursions marked 'optional' are not included in the holiday price and are payable locally </li>
<li>Gornergrat Rack Railway excursion (approx CHF 43 per person)</li>
<li>Matterhorn Glacier Paradise (approx. CHF 50 per person)</li>
<li>Any extras, drinks and personal expenses</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure for 2022 any day in the week except Tuesday</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Please note this a multicentre  and self guided holiday</li>
<li>Please ring our reservations on <a style="padding: 0px 5px; color: #00a1d8; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: transparent; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;" href="tel:01483938220" class="c-prehead-text__contact-number c-link InfinityNumber">01483 938 220</a> for prices</li>
<li>Extra nights - Optional add on extra nights in Zermatt, Grindelwald or Interlaken with a choice of hotels </li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Your Hotels</strong></p>
<p>Your first three nights will be spent at the four-star The <a data-udi="umb://document/f6750f7ff4fb484f99ab3cb1b476b335" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f6750f7ff4fb484f99ab3cb1b476b335}" title="Hotel Wilden Mann">Romantik Hotel Wilden Mann</a> in Lucerne. This is a charming, comfortable hotel located right in the heart of Lucerne's beautiful historic old town. Dating back to 1860, the hotel has many original features and the rooms are individually-styled to give a traditional charm and boutique feel. The railway station and harbour for excursions are only 8 minutes' walk away.  </p>
<p>Your hotel in St. Moritz is the lovely <a data-udi="umb://document/990d57a643344020abc9d610d2715f84" href="/{localLink:umb://document/990d57a643344020abc9d610d2715f84}" title="Hotel Monopol">Hotel Monopol</a> (which we feature in our ski programme). This welcoming hotel has a relaxed atmosphere and boasts fabulous views over the resort. It enjoys a convenient central location close to the amenities and just a short walk from the Corviglia funicular.  A little oasis of luxury with 73 spacious rooms, a rooftop spa and outstanding service. Restaurant Mono offers Italian-Mediterranean cuisine.  </p>
<p>The <a data-udi="umb://document/acb5b34744b74e408ca29b96eb446fd7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acb5b34744b74e408ca29b96eb446fd7}" title="Parkhotel Beau Site">Le Mirabeau Hotel &amp; Spa</a> in Zermatt is one of favourite within our programme. It enjoys a fantastic location just 5 minutes' walk to Zermatt's main street or to the Sunnegga lift for access to the hiking area. Guests here can marvel at some of the best views towards the Matterhorn from it's floor to ceiling glass dining room windows. Rooms are well-furnished and have a bath with overhead shower, bathrobes and slippers, satellite TV, minibar, telephone, hairdryer, radio and safe and Wi-Fi. </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure flights to Zurich from:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Heathrow, Luton, London City, Birmingham &amp; Manchester</li>
<li>Or indirect flights via Amsterdam from regional airports available on request</li>
<li>Flight supplements may apply</li>
</ul>
<p><em> The itineraries may be subject to change. Where this becomes necessary, and where practicable, we will take the steps as outlined in clause 5 of our <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/legal/terms-conditions">terms and conditions</a>.</em></p>
<p> </p>
